HEADWORD: Couscous
<hw>Cous"cous`</hw> <pr>(k??s"k??s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of food used by the natives of Western Africa, made of millet flour with flesh, and leaves of the baobab; -- called also <altname>lalo</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

